@yes316: this rip seems to use VBR(variable bitrate) to avoid wasting data space. the max kbps is 320, which is useful for full eq spectrum allocation. but VBR cuts down the bitrate during unnecessary points, such as silences, talking, or anything that doesn't use the full frequency spectrum. I'm not a fan of VBR, so when I rip the cd myself, it'll be constant 320 for sure.
